23:{t:'Slang & Particles',w:'Week 4',emoji:'✨',
  vocab:[
    {id:'Dong',en:'Please / come on (softens request)',p:'dong'},{id:'Sih',en:'Hmm / though (mild wonder)',p:'sih'},
    {id:'Lah',en:'Softens commands, adds certainty',p:'lah'},{id:'Nih',en:'Here you go / look at this',p:'nih'},
    {id:'Deh',en:'Persuasion / reluctant agreement',p:'deh'},{id:'Banget',en:'Very / so much (intensifier)',p:'bah-nget'},
    {id:'Kok',en:'Why / how come (mild surprise)',p:'kok'},{id:'Kan',en:'Right? Isn\'t it? (confirmation)',p:'kahn'},
    {id:'Gimana',en:'How? / So? (casual)',p:'gee-mah-nah'},{id:'Emang',en:'Really / indeed (casual)',p:'e-mang'}
  ],
  gr:{rule:'Particles add emotional tone — always at end of sentences',
    explain:'These sentence-final particles are what make Indonesian sound natural. "Lah" softens a command. "Dong" makes a request warmer. "Banget" intensifies. "Sih" adds surprise or wonder. They don\'t change grammar — they add FEELING.',
    ex:[{id:'Pergi lah, sudah terlambat!',en:'Just go, you\'re late!'},{id:'Kenapa sih kamu terlambat?',en:'Why are you late, though?'},{id:'Enak banget makanan ini!',en:'This food is SO delicious!'}]},
  build:{s:'Makanan ini enak banget lah!',e:'This food is SO delicious!',w:['lah!','ini','Makanan','banget','enak','dong']},
  speak:{task:'Use "dong", "lah", "banget", "sih", and "kan" in 5 natural sentences each.',dur:90,
    samples:[{id:'Tolong dong, saya butuh bantuan.',en:'Please help, I need assistance.'},{id:'Enak banget! Saya mau lagi.',en:'So delicious! I want more.'},{id:'Kenapa sih kamu tidak datang?',en:'Why didn\'t you come, though?'},{id:'Kamu sudah makan, kan?',en:'You\'ve already eaten, right?'}]},
  listen:{t:'Indonesian Comedy Skit with Particles',d:'YouTube · stand up comedy Indonesia subtitle — listen for particles!',u:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=stand+up+comedy+Indonesia+subtitle+bahasa'},
  tip:'Particles are the secret ingredient that make Indonesian sound natural. Native speakers use "lah", "dong", and "sih" constantly — use them fearlessly!'
},
24:{t:'Telling Stories',w:'Week 4',emoji:'📖',
  vocab:[
    {id:'Pertama',en:'First / firstly',p:'per-tah-mah'},{id:'Lalu',en:'Then / after that',p:'lah-loo'},
    {id:'Kemudian',en:'Subsequently / next',p:'ke-moo-dee-an'},{id:'Akhirnya',en:'Finally / in the end',p:'ahk-heer-nyah'},
    {id:'Tapi / Tetapi',en:'But (casual/formal)',p:'tah-pee / te-tah-pee'},{id:'Karena',en:'Because',p:'kah-reh-nah'},
    {id:'Jadi',en:'So / therefore',p:'jah-dee'},{id:'Sudah',en:'Already / have done',p:'soo-dah'},
    {id:'Belum',en:'Not yet',p:'beh-loom'},{id:'Pernah',en:'Have ever (experience)',p:'per-nah'},
    {id:'Tiba-tiba',en:'Suddenly',p:'tee-bah tee-bah'},{id:'Waktu itu',en:'At that time',p:'wak-too ee-too'}
  ],
  gr:{rule:'"Sudah" (have done) + "Belum" (not yet) — a perfect pair',
    explain:'"Sudah" = completed: "Saya sudah makan" (I have eaten). "Belum" = not yet: "Saya belum makan". "Pernah" = life experience: "Saya pernah ke Bali" (I\'ve been to Bali). These replace tenses for expressing completion.',
    ex:[{id:'Saya sudah pergi ke Bali.',en:'I have already been to Bali.'},{id:'Apakah kamu sudah makan?',en:'Have you eaten yet?'},{id:'Belum, saya belum makan.',en:'Not yet, I haven\'t eaten.'}]},
  build:{s:'Pertama saya makan, lalu pergi ke pasar.',e:'First I ate, then went to the market.',w:['pasar.','Pertama','saya','makan,','ke','lalu','pergi']},
  speak:{task:'Tell a story about your last weekend using: pertama, lalu, kemudian, akhirnya.',dur:120,
    samples:[{id:'Akhir pekan lalu, pertama saya bangun terlambat.',en:'Last weekend, first I woke up late.'},{id:'Lalu, saya sarapan dengan cepat.',en:'Then I had breakfast quickly.'},{id:'Kemudian saya pergi ke teman.',en:'After that I went to a friend\'s.'},{id:'Akhirnya, saya pulang dan tidur.',en:'Finally I went home and slept.'}]},
  listen:{t:'Indonesian Folk Tale Retold',d:'YouTube · cerita rakyat Indonesia animasi subtitle English',u:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=cerita+rakyat+Indonesia+animasi+subtitle+English'},
  tip:'"Sudah" and "belum" are a matched pair. If someone asks "Sudah?" and the answer is no, say "Belum!" (not "Tidak!"). This is a very natural exchange!'
},
25:{t:'Expressing Opinions',w:'Week 4',emoji:'💬',
  vocab:[
    {id:'Menurut saya',en:'In my opinion / according to me',p:'me-noo-root sah-yah'},{id:'Saya pikir',en:'I think',p:'sah-yah pee-keer'},
    {id:'Saya rasa',en:'I feel / I sense (opinion)',p:'sah-yah rah-sah'},{id:'Saya setuju',en:'I agree',p:'sah-yah se-too-joo'},
    {id:'Saya tidak setuju',en:'I disagree',p:'sah-yah tee-dak se-too-joo'},{id:'Menurut kamu?',en:'What do you think?',p:'me-noo-root kah-moo'},
    {id:'Mungkin',en:'Maybe / perhaps',p:'moong-keen'},{id:'Pasti',en:'Definitely / certainly',p:'pah-stee'},
    {id:'Penting',en:'Important',p:'pen-ting'},{id:'Menarik',en:'Interesting / attractive',p:'me-nah-reek'}
  ],
  gr:{rule:'"Menurut saya + sentence" — express any opinion diplomatically',
    explain:'"Menurut saya" literally = "according to me" — signals personal opinion, not fact. Use it constantly! It\'s a social lubricant in Indonesian conversation that shows you\'re sharing a view, not stating absolute truth.',
    ex:[{id:'Menurut saya, makanan Indonesia terbaik.',en:'In my opinion, Indonesian food is the best.'},{id:'Saya pikir belajar bahasa itu penting.',en:'I think learning languages is important.'},{id:'Menurut kamu, bagaimana?',en:'What do you think?'}]},
  build:{s:'Menurut saya, ini sangat menarik.',e:'In my opinion, this is very interesting.',w:['menarik.','saya,','Menurut','sangat','ini','penting']},
  speak:{task:'Give your opinion on 3 topics: Indonesian food, travel to Indonesia, and learning languages.',dur:120,
    samples:[{id:'Menurut saya, nasi goreng adalah makanan terbaik.',en:'In my opinion, fried rice is the best food.'},{id:'Saya pikir perjalanan ke Indonesia sangat menarik.',en:'I think a trip to Indonesia is very interesting.'},{id:'Menurut saya, belajar bahasa membuka banyak pintu.',en:'In my opinion, learning a language opens many doors.'},{id:'Menurut kamu, bahasa apa yang paling sulit?',en:'In your opinion, which language is hardest?'}]},
  listen:{t:'Indonesian Interview / Discussion',d:'YouTube · wawancara Indonesia subtitle — listen for opinion words',u:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=wawancara+Indonesia+subtitle+English+opinion'},
  tip:'"Menurut saya" is your diplomatic shield in Indonesian conversations — personalize every statement and show intellectual humility!'
},
